title.narrative: Supporting Uganda's Strategy for Acceleration Towards Elimination of Malaria

description.narrative: Uganda - Malaria - Ministry of Finance, Planning and Economic Development of the Republic of Uganda - MoFPED. This program has the following goals: By 2025, reduce malaria infection by 50%, morbidity by 50% and malaria related mortality by 75% of the 2019 levels.. The objectives of this program are: Accelerate access to malaria preventative and curative services to achieve universal coverage in all eligible populations by 2025. Enhance quality of care of malariaservices in atleast 80% of private health facilities managing malaria according to national guidelines and reporting quality data by 2025. By 2025, atleast 90% of the population sustains the the acquired knowledge, utilizes and practices correct malaria prevention, control and management measures. Malaria programming at all levels guided and based on robust data and evidence. By 2025, transform malaria programmingin targeted districts from control to elimination. By 2025, 80% of the districts will have strengthened enabling enviroment to deliver malaria inteventions and measure progress through coordinated partnership and multisectoral collaboration
